GEICO Corporation Key Developments

Angela Rinella Names Vice President of GEICO Claims
Jul 26 17
GEICO recently named Angela Rinella as vice president of claims operations at its corporate headquarters in Chevy Chase, Md. Rinella will oversee all of GEICO's claims operations. Rinella began her GEICO career in 2002, as a telephone claims representative in Woodbury, N.Y., and was part of the team that opened GEICO's regional center in Buffalo, N.Y., in 2004. She helped established the Buffalo claims department in 2005, and served in several management capacities. In 2010, Rinella became regional liability director in Lakeland, Fla. For the past three years, she has served as assistant vice president of claims in GEICO's Fredericksburg, Va., regional office.


GEICO Names Hank Nayden as Vice President, General Counsel and Legislative Counsel
Jul 22 17
GEICO has named Hank Nayden as vice president, general counsel and legislative counsel at the company’s corporate headquarters in Chevy Chase, Md. Nayden will assume responsibility for GEICO’s general counsel’s office and will continue to oversee the company’s office of legislative counsel, a role he has served in since 2000. Nayden joined GEICO in 1992, as an attorney in the legislative counsel’s office. In 1997, he was selected for the company’s Executive Assistant Program, serving in a number of rotational positions and assignments.


GEICO Names Bill Brower as Assistant Vice President of Marketing
Feb 18 17
GEICO has named Bill Brower of Arlington, Va., assistant vice president of marketing. Brower previously served as the company’s director of advertising. He has primary responsibility for leading GEICO’s partnerships with advertising and media buying agencies and oversees all aspects of GEICO’s sports, event and outdoor marketing programs. Brower joined GEICO in 1984 as a Criterion insurance counselor before taking a research analyst position in Criterion marketing.


